{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3334s","heading":"Programs for next-generation microelectronics in support of artificial intelligence","label":"3334s Programs for next-generation microelectronics in support of artificial intelligence","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/ch45/schII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2025—Subsec. (e). struck out subsec. (e) which related to briefing requirements of the Director of the Intelligence Advanced Research Projects Activity.Pub. L. 119–60","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","DefinitionsFor definitions of “intelligence community” and “congressional intelligence committees” as used in this section, see , set out as a note under .section 7002 of Pub. L. 118–31section 3003 of this title"],"amendments":["Amendments2025—Subsec. (e). struck out subsec. (e) which related to briefing requirements of the Director of the Intelligence Advanced Research Projects Activity.Pub. L. 119–60"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Program establishment","label":"a Program establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Subject to the availability of appropriations, the Director of National Intelligence, acting through the Director of the Intelligence Advanced Research Projects Activity, shall establish or otherwise oversee a program to advance microelectronics research.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Research focus","label":"b Research focus","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Advanced engineering and applied research into next-generation computing models, materials, devices, architectures, and algorithms to enable the advancement of artificial intelligence and machine learning.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"overcome challenges with engineering and applied research of microelectronics, including with respect to the physical limits on transistors, electrical interconnects, and memory elements;1So in original. Probably should be followed by “and”.1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"next-generation algorithm design;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"next-generation compute capability;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"generative and adaptive artificial intelligence for design applications;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"photonics-based microprocessors, including electrophotonics;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"v","heading":null,"label":"v","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B/v","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the chemistry and physics of new materials;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"vi","heading":null,"label":"vi","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B/vi","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fvi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"optical communication networks, including electrophotonics; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"vii","heading":null,"label":"vii","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B/vii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fvii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"safety and controls for generative artificial intelligence applications for the intelligence community.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any other activity the Director determines would promote the development of microelectronics research for future technologies, including optical communications or quantum technologies.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Consideration, consultation, and collaboration","label":"c Consideration, consultation, and collaboration","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3334s","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3334s%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":